tweet: Our phones are now fully caffeinated and ready to face the work week!  Thank you for your patience as we worked to get back online.

name: Two Rivers Public Health Department
tweet: Even phone systems don't like Mondays!  While we try to convince ours to have another cup of coffee and wake up, please email us at orders@trphd.org, or use our social media messaging to reach us.  We will update everyone when phones are sufficiently caffeinated.

name: Two Rivers Public Health Department
tweet: A new Test Nebraska site has been established in Gothenburg. The first day for testing will be Monday, August 3, from 11 am-2 pm. The location is 912 20th St. Please register at  https://t.co/8bGnaGGhh2 prior to the event.  https://t.co/BqOqe4EyTu

name: Two Rivers Public Health Department
tweet: More COVID testing will be available in Buffalo County through Test Nebraska. New days added will be Mondays and Fridays from 11 am to 1 pm beginning on Friday, July 31, at 3320 Avenue A in Kearney. Don't forget to register first at  https://t.co/8bGnaGGhh2.

tweet: As a result of inclement weather, the Test Nebraska COVID testing in Lexington today (July 22) has been cancelled. Those who have registered to test can go to the Buffalo County Fairgrounds if they are able.
